&amp;author=CP+Ho&amp;author=DL+Persson&amp;author=SB+Gay&amp;publication_year=2008&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=1571-1590&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.286075141&amp;pmid=18936022">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">4.</div><div id="r4" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Akhrass R, Yaffe MB, Brandt CP, Reigle M, Fallon WF Jr, Malangoni MA. Pancreatic trauma: a ten-year multi-institutional experience. <em>Am Surg</em> 1997;63(7):598–604.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/9202533/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Pancreatic+trauma%3A+a+ten-year+multi-institutional+experience&amp;author=R+Akhrass&amp;author=MB+Yaffe&amp;author=CP+Brandt&amp;author=M+Reigle&amp;author=WF+Fallon&amp;author=MA+Malangoni&amp;publication_year=1997&amp;journal=Am+Surg&amp;pages=598-604&amp;pmid=9202533">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">5.</div><div id="r5" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Dreizin D, Bodanapally UK, Munera F. MDCT of complications and common postoperative findings following penetrating torso trauma. <em>Emerg Radiol</em> 2015;22(5): 553–563.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10140-015-1325-6">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26013026/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=MDCT+of+complications+and+common+postoperative+findings+following+penetrating+torso+trauma&amp;author=D+Dreizin&amp;author=UK+Bodanapally&amp;author=F+Munera&amp;publication_year=2015&amp;journal=Emerg+Radiol&amp;pages=553-563&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs10140-015-1325-6&amp;pmid=26013026">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">6.</div><div id="r6" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Kuza CM, Hirji SA, Englum BR, Ganapathi AM, Speicher PJ, Scarborough JE. Pancreatic injuries in abdominal trauma in US adults: analysis of the National Trauma Data Bank on Management, Outcomes, and Predictors of Mortality. <em>Scand J Surg</em> 2020;109(3):193–204. <a href="https://doi.org/10.1177/1457496919851608">https://doi.org/10.1177/1457496919851608</a>.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31142209/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Pancreatic+injuries+in+abdominal+trauma+in+US+adults%3A+analysis+of+the+National+Trauma+Data+Bank+on+Management%2C+Outcomes%2C+and+Predictors+of+Mortality&amp;author=CM+Kuza&amp;author=SA+Hirji&amp;author=BR+Englum&amp;author=AM+Ganapathi&amp;author=PJ+Speicher&amp;author=JE+Scarborough&amp;publication_year=2020&amp;journal=Scand+J+Surg&amp;pages=193-204&amp;doi=10.1177%2F1457496919851608&amp;pmid=31142209">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">7.</div><div id="r7" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Lee PH, Lee SK, Kim GU, et al. Outcomes of hemodynamically stable patients with pancreatic injury after blunt abdominal trauma. <em>Pancreatology</em> 2012;12(6):487–492.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.pan.2012.09.006">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23217286/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Outcomes+of+hemodynamically+stable+patients+with+pancreatic+injury+after+blunt+